The mountainous region is one of the 24 most vulnerable regions on Earth in terms of nature conservation.Countries and Regions $$$ Azerbaijan, Armenia, Georgia, Russia Alania, Stavropol Territory, Chechnya), South Ossetia, Abkhazia. The climate in the Caucasus varies both vertically (altitude) and horizontally (latitude and location). Temperature usually decreases as altitude increases and approaches the sea. Average annual the temperature in Sukhum (Abkhazia) at sea level is 15 degrees Celsius, and on the slopes of Mount Kazbek, at an altitude of 3700 m, the average annual air temperature drops to -6.1 degrees Celsius.